Appendix: Glossary
Negotiated causality – the property of the system to adjust causal relationships according to user intentions.

Phantom error – a mistake that has been abandoned, but remains in a parallel timeline, with no effect on consensus.

Temporal consensus – the implicit agreement among all active users on a common timeline.

Temporal Virtual Machine (TVM) – the Flux bytecode executor, which simulates collapses and branches.

